{"pageProps":{"post":{"creator":"Evelina Judeikyte","title":"Why you should add Datawrapper to your dataviz stack","link":"https://www.theplot.media/p/why-you-should-use-datawrapper","pubDate":"Thu, 23 Jun 2022 14:04:09 GMT","content:encoded":"<p>What data visualisation tools do you use most? I love learning different softwares to be able to choose the right one for each of my projects. If I need to create a corporate dashboard, I&#8217;ll often turn to Tableau or Google Studio. For design-heavy projects, I&#8217;ll jump into Illustrator or Figma. But choosing the right tool for an outcome somewhere in between &#8212; an explanatory chart with just a gentle touch of customisation &#8212; is probably the hardest.</p><p>At the beginning of the week, I asked the Twitter community what they use in this scenario.</p><div class=\"captioned-image-container\"><figure><a class=\"image-link is-viewable-img image2\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7a17f52f-a525-4315-a688-cac1dcf1752f_1174x590.png\"><div class=\"image2-inset\"><picture><source type=\"image/webp\" srcset=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7a17f52f-a525-4315-a688-cac1dcf1752f_1174x590.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7a17f52f-a525-4315-a688-cac1dcf1752f_1174x590.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7a17f52f-a525-4315-a688-cac1dcf1752f_1174x590.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7a17f52f-a525-4315-a688-cac1dcf1752f_1174x590.png 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\"><img src=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7a17f52f-a525-4315-a688-cac1dcf1752f_1174x590.png\" width=\"590\" height=\"296.5076660988075\" data-attrs=\"{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://bucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/7a17f52f-a525-4315-a688-cac1dcf1752f_1174x590.png&quot;,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:590,&quot;width&quot;:1174,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:590,&quot;bytes&quot;:110172,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}\" class=\"sizing-normal\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7a17f52f-a525-4315-a688-cac1dcf1752f_1174x590.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7a17f52f-a525-4315-a688-cac1dcf1752f_1174x590.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7a17f52f-a525-4315-a688-cac1dcf1752f_1174x590.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7a17f52f-a525-4315-a688-cac1dcf1752f_1174x590.png 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\"></picture><div class=\"image-link-expand\"><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#FFFFFF\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-maximize2\"><polyline points=\"15 3 21 3 21 9\"></polyline><polyline points=\"9 21 3 21 3 15\"></polyline><line x1=\"21\" y1=\"3\" x2=\"14\" y2=\"10\"></line><line x1=\"3\" y1=\"21\" x2=\"10\" y2=\"14\"></line></svg></div></div></a><figcaption class=\"image-caption\">See full poll results on <a href=\"https://twitter.com/evelinajud/status/1538877997003984901?s=20&amp;t=XK3g3iLm0HEa6bDWmNrk2A\">Twitter</a></figcaption></figure></div><p>As you can see from the poll above, RawGraphs got the most votes. Kudos to them! Today I want to talk to you about a less popular open-source tool I think we should use more often.</p><p><a href=\"https://www.datawrapper.de/\">Datawrapper</a>. </p><p>Datawrapper allows you to create beautiful charts and maps and tailor them to your liking quite a bit. I&#8217;ll use a personal example to illustrate some of its coolest features. At the beginning of 2022, I challenged myself to lose 5kg (be gone, Covid weight!). I tracked my progress every day since January 1st and visualised it using Datawrapper. The result is a pretty simple line chart with three custom touches to it. Let&#8217;s unpack them one by one.</p><div class=\"captioned-image-container\"><figure><a class=\"image-link is-viewable-img image2\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F768cecae-89a8-495a-bb73-9dd559837c4c_1626x1156.png\"><div class=\"image2-inset\"><picture><source type=\"image/webp\" srcset=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F768cecae-89a8-495a-bb73-9dd559837c4c_1626x1156.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F768cecae-89a8-495a-bb73-9dd559837c4c_1626x1156.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F768cecae-89a8-495a-bb73-9dd559837c4c_1626x1156.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F768cecae-89a8-495a-bb73-9dd559837c4c_1626x1156.png 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\"><img src=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F768cecae-89a8-495a-bb73-9dd559837c4c_1626x1156.png\" width=\"728\" height=\"517.5\" data-attrs=\"{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://bucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/768cecae-89a8-495a-bb73-9dd559837c4c_1626x1156.png&quot;,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:false,&quot;imageSize&quot;:&quot;normal&quot;,&quot;height&quot;:1035,&quot;width&quot;:1456,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:728,&quot;bytes&quot;:113479,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;A line chart showing daily weight figures from January to June 2022, and highlighting that I reached my weight goal in April.&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}\" class=\"sizing-normal\" alt=\"A line chart showing daily weight figures from January to June 2022, and highlighting that I reached my weight goal in April.\" title=\"A line chart showing daily weight figures from January to June 2022, and highlighting that I reached my weight goal in April.\" srcset=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F768cecae-89a8-495a-bb73-9dd559837c4c_1626x1156.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F768cecae-89a8-495a-bb73-9dd559837c4c_1626x1156.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F768cecae-89a8-495a-bb73-9dd559837c4c_1626x1156.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F768cecae-89a8-495a-bb73-9dd559837c4c_1626x1156.png 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\"></picture><div class=\"image-link-expand\"><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#FFFFFF\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-maximize2\"><polyline points=\"15 3 21 3 21 9\"></polyline><polyline points=\"9 21 3 21 3 15\"></polyline><line x1=\"21\" y1=\"3\" x2=\"14\" y2=\"10\"></line><line x1=\"3\" y1=\"21\" x2=\"10\" y2=\"14\"></line></svg></div></div></a><figcaption class=\"image-caption\">Showing off some of the coolest Datawrapper features on a basic line chart.</figcaption></figure></div><h3>1. Customising an axis</h3><p>Chart axes are important for understanding what&#8217;s going on, but let&#8217;s be honest &#8212; most tools make them look uninspiring. Which is why I love that Datawrapper allows you to refine the frequency of the axis ticks, and even place the values above the gridlines for a more compact look! </p><p>You can see how I adjusted the vertical axis of the fitness chart in the GIF below.</p><div class=\"captioned-image-container\"><figure><a class=\"image-link is-viewable-img image2\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F99cb106f-177d-40d5-b3c0-b2792e6ffc60_1368x878.gif\"><div class=\"image2-inset\"><picture><source type=\"image/webp\" srcset=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F99cb106f-177d-40d5-b3c0-b2792e6ffc60_1368x878.gif 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F99cb106f-177d-40d5-b3c0-b2792e6ffc60_1368x878.gif 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F99cb106f-177d-40d5-b3c0-b2792e6ffc60_1368x878.gif 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F99cb106f-177d-40d5-b3c0-b2792e6ffc60_1368x878.gif 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\"><img src=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F99cb106f-177d-40d5-b3c0-b2792e6ffc60_1368x878.gif\" width=\"1368\" height=\"878\" data-attrs=\"{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://bucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/99cb106f-177d-40d5-b3c0-b2792e6ffc60_1368x878.gif&quot;,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:878,&quot;width&quot;:1368,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:1010264,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;A GIF showing how to adjust the frequency of axis ticks and their placement in the refine section of Datawrapper.&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/gif&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}\" class=\"sizing-normal\" alt=\"A GIF showing how to adjust the frequency of axis ticks and their placement in the refine section of Datawrapper.\" title=\"A GIF showing how to adjust the frequency of axis ticks and their placement in the refine section of Datawrapper.\" srcset=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F99cb106f-177d-40d5-b3c0-b2792e6ffc60_1368x878.gif 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F99cb106f-177d-40d5-b3c0-b2792e6ffc60_1368x878.gif 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F99cb106f-177d-40d5-b3c0-b2792e6ffc60_1368x878.gif 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F99cb106f-177d-40d5-b3c0-b2792e6ffc60_1368x878.gif 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\" loading=\"lazy\"></picture><div class=\"image-link-expand\"><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#FFFFFF\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-maximize2\"><polyline points=\"15 3 21 3 21 9\"></polyline><polyline points=\"9 21 3 21 3 15\"></polyline><line x1=\"21\" y1=\"3\" x2=\"14\" y2=\"10\"></line><line x1=\"3\" y1=\"21\" x2=\"10\" y2=\"14\"></line></svg></div></div></a><figcaption class=\"image-caption\">Adjusting the vertical axis to make it cleaner, nicer and save some space.</figcaption></figure></div><h3>2. Highlighting a point</h3><p>Adding text comments to visualisations is my favourite discrete way of providing additional context to the readers. But I don&#8217;t always want to open Illustrator just to write some text. Datawrapper has solved that pain point &#8212; it allows you to add as many annotations as you&#8217;d like and format them. The process is (almost) hassle free! In the chart below, I added a shout out for the day I reached my weight goal.</p><p><em>Extra tip: Did you notice that I also used the annotation function to add explanations to the 0 and 5 values on the vertical axis?</em></p><div class=\"captioned-image-container\"><figure><a class=\"image-link is-viewable-img image2\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F01995822-9f55-4106-8fab-fd76b037386e_1382x808.gif\"><div class=\"image2-inset\"><picture><source type=\"image/webp\" srcset=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F01995822-9f55-4106-8fab-fd76b037386e_1382x808.gif 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F01995822-9f55-4106-8fab-fd76b037386e_1382x808.gif 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F01995822-9f55-4106-8fab-fd76b037386e_1382x808.gif 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F01995822-9f55-4106-8fab-fd76b037386e_1382x808.gif 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\"><img src=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F01995822-9f55-4106-8fab-fd76b037386e_1382x808.gif\" width=\"1382\" height=\"808\" data-attrs=\"{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://bucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/01995822-9f55-4106-8fab-fd76b037386e_1382x808.gif&quot;,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:808,&quot;width&quot;:1382,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:3272607,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/gif&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}\" class=\"sizing-normal\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F01995822-9f55-4106-8fab-fd76b037386e_1382x808.gif 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F01995822-9f55-4106-8fab-fd76b037386e_1382x808.gif 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F01995822-9f55-4106-8fab-fd76b037386e_1382x808.gif 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F01995822-9f55-4106-8fab-fd76b037386e_1382x808.gif 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\" loading=\"lazy\"></picture><div class=\"image-link-expand\"><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#FFFFFF\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-maximize2\"><polyline points=\"15 3 21 3 21 9\"></polyline><polyline points=\"9 21 3 21 3 15\"></polyline><line x1=\"21\" y1=\"3\" x2=\"14\" y2=\"10\"></line><line x1=\"3\" y1=\"21\" x2=\"10\" y2=\"14\"></line></svg></div></div></a><figcaption class=\"image-caption\">Adding annotations to highlight an important data point, as well as explain the vertical axis values.</figcaption></figure></div><h3>3. Highlighting a period of time</h3><p>Annotations are great for calling out single points in time. But sometimes we also want to highlight longer periods &#8212; to draw the reader&#8217;s attention to missing data or forecasts, for example. Yes, you&#8217;ve guessed it, Datawrapper has that feature too! You can select the area to highlight and adjust its colour. In the fitness chart we&#8217;re looking at today, I highlighted the missing data &#8212; the weeks during which I didn&#8217;t have access to a scale.</p><div class=\"captioned-image-container\"><figure><a class=\"image-link is-viewable-img image2\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2afde8ee-fcec-4549-b7ce-1ef346801cf8_1382x808.gif\"><div class=\"image2-inset\"><picture><source type=\"image/webp\" srcset=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2afde8ee-fcec-4549-b7ce-1ef346801cf8_1382x808.gif 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2afde8ee-fcec-4549-b7ce-1ef346801cf8_1382x808.gif 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2afde8ee-fcec-4549-b7ce-1ef346801cf8_1382x808.gif 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2afde8ee-fcec-4549-b7ce-1ef346801cf8_1382x808.gif 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\"><img src=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2afde8ee-fcec-4549-b7ce-1ef346801cf8_1382x808.gif\" width=\"1382\" height=\"808\" data-attrs=\"{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://bucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/2afde8ee-fcec-4549-b7ce-1ef346801cf8_1382x808.gif&quot;,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:808,&quot;width&quot;:1382,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:727838,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;A GIF showing how to use the highlight range feature in Datawrapper's annotate section.&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/gif&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}\" class=\"sizing-normal\" alt=\"A GIF showing how to use the highlight range feature in Datawrapper's annotate section.\" title=\"A GIF showing how to use the highlight range feature in Datawrapper's annotate section.\" srcset=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2afde8ee-fcec-4549-b7ce-1ef346801cf8_1382x808.gif 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2afde8ee-fcec-4549-b7ce-1ef346801cf8_1382x808.gif 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2afde8ee-fcec-4549-b7ce-1ef346801cf8_1382x808.gif 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2afde8ee-fcec-4549-b7ce-1ef346801cf8_1382x808.gif 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\" loading=\"lazy\"></picture><div class=\"image-link-expand\"><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#FFFFFF\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-maximize2\"><polyline points=\"15 3 21 3 21 9\"></polyline><polyline points=\"9 21 3 21 3 15\"></polyline><line x1=\"21\" y1=\"3\" x2=\"14\" y2=\"10\"></line><line x1=\"3\" y1=\"21\" x2=\"10\" y2=\"14\"></line></svg></div></div></a><figcaption class=\"image-caption\">Adding a range highlight to call out chunks of missing data.</figcaption></figure></div><p>These are just some of the fun features Datawrapper has to offer. If you&#8217;re intrigued, you can check their <a href=\"https://academy.datawrapper.de/\">academy page</a> to learn more (it&#8217;s free!). </p><div><hr></div><p>If you typically use BI tools to create explanatory charts, I dare you try out Datawrapper next time! If you&#8217;re already a user of the tool, what is your favourite functionality? Let us know in the comments. &#128578;</p><p>Thanks for reading The Plot!</p><p>See you in two weeks,</p><p>Evelina</p>","content:encodedSnippet":"What data visualisation tools do you use most? I love learning different softwares to be able to choose the right one for each of my projects. If I need to create a corporate dashboard, Iâ€™ll often turn to Tableau or Google Studio. For design-heavy projects, Iâ€™ll jump into Illustrator or Figma. But choosing the right tool for an outcome somewhere in between â€” an explanatory chart with just a gentle touch of customisation â€” is probably the hardest.\nAt the beginning of the week, I asked the Twitter community what they use in this scenario.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nSee full poll results on Twitter\nAs you can see from the poll above, RawGraphs got the most votes. Kudos to them! Today I want to talk to you about a less popular open-source tool I think we should use more often.\nDatawrapper. \nDatawrapper allows you to create beautiful charts and maps and tailor them to your liking quite a bit. Iâ€™ll use a personal example to illustrate some of its coolest features. At the beginning of 2022, I challenged myself to lose 5kg (be gone, Covid weight!). I tracked my progress every day since January 1st and visualised it using Datawrapper. The result is a pretty simple line chart with three custom touches to it. Letâ€™s unpack them one by one.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nShowing off some of the coolest Datawrapper features on a basic line chart.\n1. Customising an axis\nChart axes are important for understanding whatâ€™s going on, but letâ€™s be honest â€” most tools make them look uninspiring. Which is why I love that Datawrapper allows you to refine the frequency of the axis ticks, and even place the values above the gridlines for a more compact look! \nYou can see how I adjusted the vertical axis of the fitness chart in the GIF below.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nAdjusting the vertical axis to make it cleaner, nicer and save some space.\n2. Highlighting a point\nAdding text comments to visualisations is my favourite discrete way of providing additional context to the readers. But I donâ€™t always want to open Illustrator just to write some text. Datawrapper has solved that pain point â€” it allows you to add as many annotations as youâ€™d like and format them. The process is (almost) hassle free! In the chart below, I added a shout out for the day I reached my weight goal.\nExtra tip: Did you notice that I also used the annotation function to add explanations to the 0 and 5 values on the vertical axis?\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nAdding annotations to highlight an important data point, as well as explain the vertical axis values.\n3. Highlighting a period of time\nAnnotations are great for calling out single points in time. But sometimes we also want to highlight longer periods â€” to draw the readerâ€™s attention to missing data or forecasts, for example. Yes, youâ€™ve guessed it, Datawrapper has that feature too! You can select the area to highlight and adjust its colour. In the fitness chart weâ€™re looking at today, I highlighted the missing data â€” the weeks during which I didnâ€™t have access to a scale.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nAdding a range highlight to call out chunks of missing data.\nThese are just some of the fun features Datawrapper has to offer. If youâ€™re intrigued, you can check their academy page to learn more (itâ€™s free!). \n\n\nIf you typically use BI tools to create explanatory charts, I dare you try out Datawrapper next time! If youâ€™re already a user of the tool, what is your favourite functionality? Let us know in the comments. ðŸ™‚\nThanks for reading The Plot!\nSee you in two weeks,\nEvelina","enclosure":{"url":"https://bucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/a06d566f-c69a-4074-a083-31a2933b751d_1382x808.gif","length":"0","type":"image/jpeg"},"dc:creator":"Evelina Judeikyte","content":"An unsponsored review of my three favorite Datawrapper features for explanatory data visualisations","contentSnippet":"An unsponsored review of my three favorite Datawrapper features for explanatory data visualisations","guid":"https://www.theplot.media/p/why-you-should-use-datawrapper","isoDate":"2022-06-23T14:04:09.000Z","itunes":{},"blogTitle":"The Plot","img":"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_256,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F4b01a32b-0a20-4073-982f-f2d1d27146b4_1025x1025.png"}},"__N_SSG":true}